OAO  Raspadskaya (RASP)  gained for the first
session in four after Interfax reported OAO Novolipetsk Steel is
considering acquiring the coal producer.  The shares climbed 2.1 percent to 169.40 rubles by the 6:45
p.m. close in Moscow, while Novolipetsk added 2.3 percent to
103.28 rubles, its biggest gain in more than three weeks.  Novolipetsk is studying Raspadskaya after 80 percent of the
company was offered for sale, Interfax reported, citing an
unidentified person with knowledge of the talks.  The person didnâ€™t say whether Novolipetsk Steel had made
any price offer, the news service said. Anton Bazulev, a
spokesman for Novolipetsk Steel, declined to comment when called
